  "text": "Capital-constrained supply chain coordination by supply chain contracts provides a novel perspective for trade credit research. Lee and Rhee [CITATION_1] show that under inventory financing costs, supply chain contracts including all-unit quantity discount contract, buyback contract, two-part tariff and revenue sharing contract can coordinate the supply chain only when the supplier provide trade credit to the retailer. Kouvelis and Zhao [20] analyze the use of revenue-sharing contract with working capital coordination for decentralized management of supply chains when there are bankruptcy risks and default costs.",
